    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Receivable

    public abstract class AbstractReceivable
extends Item
implements IReceivable

    A data-access layer data-transfer object for the Receivable. This class is an abstract class that contains AndroMDA generated code; change nothing in this class. Instead, override any methods in the concrete subclass generated in the same package. AndroMDA will overwrite this class each time you run it but will never overwrite the concrete subclass.

    Stereotypes:

    • Persistent

    Class is read/write: true

        Create a Receivable. The concrete subclass must call this constructor.
        Parameters:
        key - the primary key of the Receivable
        orderNumber -
        transactionId - composite super-key attribute that uniquely identifies child combined with child sub-key and any other parent super-keys
        amount - the monetary amount in dollars of the transaction item
        debit - whether the item is a debit (true) or credit (false); default value is the debit-default value of the account
        checked - whether the value and details of the transaction item have been verified and reconciled
        accountName - foreign key used by setter to query associated object
        entityName - foreign key used by setter to query associated object
